40|$|This report {{lays out}} generic {{scenarios}} for <b>balancing</b> <b>the</b> <b>budget</b> <b>in</b> <b>the</b> next fiscal year. Although {{these are not}} policy options {{that are likely to}} be enacted, they are meant to offer simple examples to gauge the scope of tradeoffs that would be required if policymakers eventually decide to bring <b>the</b> <b>budget</b> back to <b>balance.</b> If changes are postponed or stretched over a longer time period, they would need to be larger because of higher debt service...|$|R
