50|$|Coming into office, one of Brown’s {{priorities}} was {{to perform}} rigorous performance audits to help <b>balance</b> <b>the</b> <b>budget.</b> <b>In</b> 2008, {{for every dollar}} the State spent, performance audits returned $8 in cost savings. In 2010, Brown reported she delivered $64 in cost savings and efficiencies for every dollar invested in the Division.|$|E
